            <title>[HIVE-25741] HiveProtoLoggingHook EventLogger should always close old writer</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-25741</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If&#160;&lt;tt&gt;hive.hook.proto.file.per.event=true&lt;/tt&gt;&#160;(recommended for S3A filesystem), the Hive proto&#160;&lt;tt&gt;EventLogger&lt;/tt&gt;&#160;will create a new file for each proto event. However, if we already had an appropriate writer (i.e. maybeRolloverWriterForDay() returns false) from some previous operation - we don&apos;t close the previous writer instance before creating a new one.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
